  "texts": [
    "Our analyses uncover some interesting insights.",
    "For both language pairs, we find a significant increase in the number of voluntary commits: Python packages by 37.05% compared to R ones, and Rust packages by 54.43% vs. Haskell packages.",
    "Regarding the type of innovation, we find that, whereas all types of commits increase significantly across both language pairs, the absolute impact is consistently larger for commits without a new function creation or commits that are maintenance related.",
    "These findings document a shift in the trajectory of innovation towards iterative refinement of existing features.",
    "The investigation into the distribution of contributions based on user activity footprint reveals that new contributions are disproportionately skewed towards packages with more user activity."
  ],
